02/11/2006
LARNACA, Cyprus -- Bulgaria, Cyprus, Greece and Romania are expected to seal a technical agreement establishing a new EU battle group later this month. The signing is scheduled for November 13th in Brussels. An announcement to that effect followed a meeting in Larnaca on Wednesday (November 1st) between Bulgarian Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov and Cypriot counterpart Nikos Simeonidis. Bliznakov stopped there after visiting the Bulgarian frigate "Drazki", deployed with the UN force in Lebanon. 
In other news Wednesday, Serbian Army deputy chief Major General Zdravko Ponos arrived in Sofia for a three-day visit. Issues related to bilateral military co-operation top the agenda. (Sega - 02/11/06; BNR, BTA, Mediapool - 01/11/06)
